name: ubiquitous
meaning: present, appearing, or found everywhere

name: alacrity
meaning: brisk and cheerful readiness

name: influenza
meaning: a highly contagious viral infection of the respiratory passages causing fever, severe aching, and catarrh, and often occurring in epidemics.

name: miserable
meaning: wretchedly unhappy or uncomfortable

name: sorrowful
meaning: feeling or showing grief

name: mother
meaning: a woman in relation to a child or children to whom she has given birth

name: lemon
meaning: a yellow, oval citrus fruit with thick skin and fragrant, acidic juice

name: honey
meaning: a sweet, sticky, yellowish-brown fluid made by bees and other insects from nectar collected from flowers

name: liquid
meaning: having a consistency like that of water or oil, i.e., flowing freely but of constant volume

name: cheetah
meaning: a large spotted cat found in Africa and parts of Asia. It is the fastest animal on land

name: pelican
meaning: a large gregarious waterbird with a long bill, an extensible throat pouch for scooping up fish, and mainly white or gray plumage

name: engineer
meaning: a person who designs, builds, or maintains engines, machines, or public works.

name: adulation
meaning: obsequious flattery; excessive admiration or praise

name: ecstatic
meaning: feeling or expressing overwhelming happiness or joyful excitement

name: tiger
meaning: a very large solitary cat with a yellow-brown coat striped with black, native to the forests of Asia but becoming increasingly rare

name: crow
meaning: a large perching bird with mostly glossy black plumage, a heavy bill, and a raucous voice.

name: knight
meaning: a man who served his sovereign or lord as a mounted soldier in armor

name: plumber
meaning: a person who installs and repairs the pipes and fittings of water supply, sanitation, or heating systems

name: programmer
meaning: a person who writes computer programs.

name: infantry
meaning: soldiers marching or fighting on foot; foot soldiers collectively

name: kettle
meaning: a vessel, usually made of metal and with a handle, used for boiling liquids or cooking foods

name: fork
meaning: an implement with two or more prongs used for lifting food to the mouth or holding it when cutting

name: flexibility
meaning: the quality of bending easily without breaking

name: despondent
meaning: in low spirits from loss of hope or courage

name: bully
meaning: a person who uses strength or power to harm or intimidate those who are weaker.

name: pincers
meaning: a tool made of two pieces of metal bearing blunt concave jaws that are arranged like the blades of scissors, used for gripping and pulling things

name: gullible
meaning: easily persuaded to believe something; credulous

name: guitar
meaning: a stringed musical instrument with a fretted fingerboard, typically incurved sides, and six or twelve strings, played by plucking or strumming with the fingers or a plectrum.

name: pineapple
meaning: a large juicy tropical fruit consisting of aromatic edible yellow flesh surrounded by a tough segmented skin and topped with a tuft of stiff leaves

name: bias
meaning: prejudice in favor of or against one thing, person, or group compared with another, usually in a way considered to be unfair
